spec: dc2881
version: ">=3.9"
backend: python_module(decimal)
error_model: python_exceptions

docs: https://docs.python.org/3/library/decimal.html

provenance:
  derived_from:
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/decimal.html — decimal module documentation"
    - "Test vectors verified with Python 3.14.4 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-13"
  not_derived_from:
    - "zspecs/decimal_extra2866.zspec.zsdl — wave 638 predecessor (covered __rand__, __ror__, __rxor__)"
    - "CPython source: Modules/_decimal/_decimal.c"
    - "CPython source: Lib/_pydecimal.py"
  notes:
    - "Wave 639 theme: __iadd__, __isub__, __imul__ dict-presence checks (in-place augmented assignment operators)."
    - "decimal.Decimal is an immutable numeric type — it does NOT define in-place operators (__iadd__, __isub__, __imul__)."
    - "Immutability means Python's augmented assignment (e.g. d += x) rebinds the name rather than mutating the object; no __iadd__ is needed or defined."
    - "decimal.Context is a mutable configuration object but defines no arithmetic in-place operators on itself."
    - "decimal exception hierarchy classes (DecimalException and all subclasses) do NOT define any in-place arithmetic operators."
    - "Absence is uniform across all decimal types — consistent with Decimal's immutable design."
    - "All expected values verified with Python 3.14.4 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-13."
  created_at: "2026-04-13"

